<p>This is a script to find appartments in an optimal location with to desired nearby locations.</p>
<pre>This is the structure of the parameter file</pre>
<pre>
School:         34.138840, -118.125094,    a*r.^2+b*r,    {a,b},    [2,1]
Climbing:       34.057231, -118.240315,    a*r.^2+b*r,    {a,b},    [1,1]
Hiking:         34.205153, -118.128317,    a*r.^2+b*r,    {a,b},    [1,1]
Downtown_LA:    34.052249, -118.242911,    a/r,           {a},      [0.01]
</pre>

<h2>Get the information from the parameter file<a name="2"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

data = parseLocations(filename);
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Generate the cost function<a name="3"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

func = @(x,y) 0*x+0*y;
for i = 1:size(data,1)
    func = @(x,y)func(x,y) + data{i,4}(sqrt((x-data{i,2}).^2+(y-data{i,3}).^2));
end
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Plot the cost function<a name="4"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

[x,y] = meshgrid(33.5:0.01:34.5,-118.5:0.01:-118);
z = func(x,y);
surf(z)
{% endhighlight %}

<h2>Find the optimal location<a name="5"></a></h2>
{% highlight matlab %}

fmin_f = @(x) func(x(1),x(2));
optimal = fminsearch(fmin_f,[0,0]);
loc = char(vpa(optimal,10));
{% endhighlight %}
<h2>Open up google maps and zillow<a name="6"></a></h2>
<p>This opens the webpages to show the optimal location with respect to the nearby locations, and apartments in the area</p>

{% highlight matlab %}

maps = ['https://www.google.com/maps/place/' loc(10:end-3)];
web(maps,'-browser')
small = sprintf('%.6f,%.6f', (vpa(optimal+radius,6)));
big = sprintf('%.6f,%.6f', (vpa(optimal-radius,6)));
loc = [small ',' big];
zillow = ['https://www.zillow.com/homes/for_rent/Pasadena-CA/apartment_duplex_type/' loc '_rect'];
web(zillow,'-browser')

function ret = parseLocations(fn)
syms a b c r
fh = fopen(fn);
line = fgetl(fh);
ret = [];
while line ~=-1
if ~strcmp(line(1),'#')
        elem = strsplit(line);
        elem{1} = elem{1}(1:end-1);
        elem{2} = str2num(elem{2}(1:end-1));
        elem{3} = str2num(elem{3}(1:end-1));
        elem{4} = matlabFunction(subs(matlabFunction(str2sym(elem{4})),eval(elem{5}), eval(elem{6})));
        ret = [ret; elem];
end
    line = fgetl(fh);
end
fclose(fh);
end
